The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Hashim Amla is recalled 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Hashim Amla is recalled 
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Test regular Hashim Amla was on Wednesday included in the South African squad for the one-off Twenty20 international against India to be played at Moses Mabhida Stadium, here, on January 9 next year, according to a Cricket South Africa media release.         
	Amla, who will make only his third appearance in the shortest format of the game, has been named in place of Loots Bosman from the squad that won their last T20 series 2-0 against Pakistan.         
	Jacques Kallis, Dale Steyn and Morne Morkel have been rested.         
	The squad: Johan Botha (capt), Hashim Amla, AB de Villiers, JP Duminy, Colin Ingram, David Miller, Makhaya Ntini, Wayne Parnell, Robin Peterson, Graeme Smith, Rusty Theron, Lonwabo Tsotsobe.                                                                                                                     
